<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0823 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Federal Minister for Research and Technology intends to publish astatement on the status and prospects of renewable energy sources. Researchand development currently flows on the following subjects: Photovoltaicenergy conversion; solar low-temperature heat; solar high-temperatureheat; wind power; biomass; storage systems. The public interest in renewableenergy technologies has increased after the Chernobyl accident. Solarheat has already reached the commercial stage, and wind energy is consideredto be economically efficient. The performance factors of heat pumps arepresented in diagrams. In general, public energy is accused of neglectingthe practical application of renewable energy sources. (HWJ).</TEXT></DOC>